WEBVTT

00:01.274 --> 00:03.907
<i>(Michael) My name is Michael Westen.</i>
<i>I used to be a spy until...</i>

00:03.908 --> 00:05.275
[ Cellphone rings ]

00:05.343 --> 00:07.077
Man: We got a burn notice
on you. You're blacklisted.

00:07.145 --> 00:08.579
[ Whistles ]

00:08.646 --> 00:10.847
<i>When you're burned,</i>
<i>you've got nothing --</i>

00:10.915 --> 00:13.116
<i>no cash, no credit,</i>
<i>no job history.</i>

00:13.184 --> 00:15.519
<i>You're stuck in whatever city</i>
<i>they decide to dump you in.</i>

00:15.587 --> 00:17.421
- Where am I?
- Miami.

00:17.488 --> 00:20.223
<i>You do whatever work</i>
<i>comes your way.</i>

00:20.291 --> 00:22.292
<i>You rely on anyone</i>
<i>who's still talking to you.</i>

00:22.360 --> 00:23.260
[ Laughs ]

00:23.328 --> 00:24.795
<i>A trigger-happy girlfriend...</i>

00:24.862 --> 00:26.430
Should we shoot them?

00:26.497 --> 00:28.231
<i>...an old friend who used</i>
<i>to inform on you to the FBI...</i>

00:28.299 --> 00:31.001
You know spies --
a bunch of bitchy little girls.

00:31.069 --> 00:33.370
<i>...family, too...</i>
<i>Hey, is that your mom again?</i>

00:33.438 --> 00:35.305
<i>...if you're desperate....</i>
<i>Someone needs your help, Michael.</i>

00:35.373 --> 00:38.442
<i>...and a down-and-out spy</i>
<i>you met along the way.</i>

00:38.509 --> 00:40.077
That's how we do it,
people.

00:40.144 --> 00:42.746
<i>Bottom line --</i>
<i>as long as you're burned,</i>

00:42.814 --> 00:44.615
<i>you're not going anywhere.</i>

00:47.836 --> 00:49.568
Ayn, I need something.

00:51.115 --> 00:52.151
I need to disappear.

00:52.151 --> 00:54.703
I might be able to arrange for
you to have a little privacy.

00:54.866 --> 00:58.720
If you hide me, I think it's only fair
that you be the one to find me.

00:59.248 --> 01:01.463
That kind of cooperation could
knock years off my sentence.

01:01.985 --> 01:03.943
Card:
Say hello to Tyler Gray

01:04.043 --> 01:05.711
the man who murdered
your brother.

01:05.807 --> 01:06.871
It's Gray!

01:06.872 --> 01:07.768
[ Grunts ]

01:07.768 --> 01:09.169
Don't move.

01:09.236 --> 01:10.937
I got him.

01:11.005 --> 01:12.612
Now we just sit wait
for Card's extraction team.

01:12.436 --> 01:14.838
Card isn't sending you
an extraction team.

01:14.905 --> 01:16.005
How do you know
about Card?

01:16.073 --> 01:17.373
Who do you think
sent me out here?

01:17.398 --> 01:19.553
This was supposed to be
a suicide mission for you.

01:19.578 --> 01:21.168
Michael: <i>That he played both of us.</i>

01:21.193 --> 01:22.432
Card: What happened
to the targets?

01:22.457 --> 01:24.949
I have people looking --
they can't find a trace.

01:24.974 --> 01:27.046
What, you think I forgot
everything you taught me?

01:27.071 --> 01:29.375
I'm saying
Michael Westen is dead.

01:29.400 --> 01:30.823
I'm proud of you, kid.

01:30.848 --> 01:34.248
<font color=#00FF00>Burn Notice 6x12</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>Means & Ends</font>
Original Air Date on November 8, 2012

01:34.249 --> 01:37.749
== sync, corrected by <font color="#00ff00">elderman</font> ==

01:37.781 --> 01:39.482
Do you ever wonder
what it would be like --

01:39.484 --> 01:42.452
actually getting to enjoy
an afternoon like this?

01:42.520 --> 01:44.554
I'm sorry. Who are you?

01:44.622 --> 01:46.657
I came here with my boyfriend,
Michael Westen.

01:46.724 --> 01:49.626
I need a rest as much
as you do, Fi -- believe me.

01:49.694 --> 01:51.261
I'm glad
to hear you say that.

01:51.329 --> 01:54.131
You've been getting about as
much sleep as a P.O.W. lately.

01:54.198 --> 01:56.066
Admitting there's a problem
is the first step.

01:58.336 --> 02:00.937
After we take Card down,
what do you say we go --

02:01.005 --> 02:02.406
[ rustling ]

02:02.473 --> 02:04.474
Hey. Whoa. Whoa. Whoa.
It's just me.

02:04.542 --> 02:06.510
It's true.
He came alone.

02:06.577 --> 02:07.778
What?
You brought a lookout?

02:07.845 --> 02:09.312
More like backup.

02:09.380 --> 02:11.181
It's almost like
you guys don't trust me.

02:11.249 --> 02:12.149
We were supposed to
lay low.

02:12.216 --> 02:13.517
Why did you want to meet?

02:13.584 --> 02:15.752
Card reached out to me.
He's getting comfortable.

02:15.820 --> 02:17.921
I mean, obviously,
nobody found your bodies.

02:17.989 --> 02:20.891
He's starting to think
that the F-18 incinerated you.

02:20.958 --> 02:22.959
So, he wants me to do the same
to your loft.

02:23.027 --> 02:24.561
He told me
to search your place

02:24.629 --> 02:27.631
for anything connected
to this mess and then burn it.

02:27.699 --> 02:28.865
You've got to be
kidding me.

02:28.933 --> 02:31.635
Michael,
you can't expect me to play dead

02:31.703 --> 02:33.603
while this bastard
turns everything we own

02:33.671 --> 02:34.905
into a pile of ash.

02:34.972 --> 02:36.440
Fi,
this is a huge break.

02:36.507 --> 02:39.109
We get to feed Card whatever
information we want him to have.

02:40.778 --> 02:42.746
Do you want to hold on
to all of our old stuff,

02:42.814 --> 02:44.314
or do you want to
nail Card to the wall?

02:44.339 --> 02:48.339
<font color=#00FF00>Burn Notice 6x12</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>Means & Ends</font>
Original Air Date on November 8, 2012

02:49.087 --> 02:51.421
Fine.

02:51.489 --> 02:56.526
But I'm not letting him
ransack and torch our home.

02:56.594 --> 02:57.761
We'll do it together.

02:57.786 --> 03:01.786
== sync, corrected by <font color="#00ff00">elderman</font> ==

03:03.801 --> 03:07.137
<i>Planting false information</i>
<i>for an enemy to find</i>

03:07.205 --> 03:08.605
<i>is a subtle art.</i>

03:08.673 --> 03:10.807
<i>There has to be</i>
<i>enough solid information</i>

03:10.875 --> 03:12.275
<i>to make it seem credible,</i>

03:12.343 --> 03:14.778
<i>but not so much</i>
<i>it can be verified.</i>

03:14.846 --> 03:17.247
<i>Do it right, and you can make</i>
<i>your target so paranoid,</i>

03:17.315 --> 03:18.482
<i>they'll be ready to crack.</i>

03:18.549 --> 03:19.916
All right.

03:19.984 --> 03:22.052
This should look like
we're just a few steps away

03:22.120 --> 03:23.653
from connecting
Anson to Card.

03:23.721 --> 03:26.623
Looks legit.
You think there's enough here?

03:26.691 --> 03:29.526
Believe me -- questions are
scarier than answers.

03:29.594 --> 03:31.595
You help him connect the dots,
show him how worried you are,

03:31.662 --> 03:33.063
you can push
for more intel.

03:33.097 --> 03:34.564
How many many of these
do I get to take?

03:34.632 --> 03:36.600
Oh, I don't know, Fi.
Two or three?

03:36.667 --> 03:39.836
It has to look like
all of our stuff has burned,

03:39.904 --> 03:42.139
so... all of our stuff
has to burn.

03:42.206 --> 03:43.073
[ Sighs ]

03:43.141 --> 03:44.274
[ Knock on door ]

03:44.342 --> 03:45.742
What the hell was that?

03:45.810 --> 03:47.444
I thought nobody knew you were back.
Nobody does.

03:47.512 --> 03:50.447
But most people
don't know we're dead, either.

03:52.000 --> 03:58.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:59.190 --> 04:00.824
And a good evening to you,
too.

04:00.892 --> 04:02.793
What are you doing here?
You know her?

04:02.860 --> 04:05.128
I'm Ayn. We go back.

04:05.196 --> 04:08.131
All the way back
to Allarod federal penitentiary.

04:08.199 --> 04:09.499
I just got out.

04:09.567 --> 04:11.334
Criminal,
I got a serious problem.

04:11.402 --> 04:12.469
You and I need to talk.

04:18.910 --> 04:20.076
It's Michael, right?

04:20.144 --> 04:22.077
I heard a bit about you
from this one.

04:22.146 --> 04:23.580
Looks like
she wasn't lying.

04:23.648 --> 04:24.815
Who is this person?

04:24.882 --> 04:26.650
How -- how did you know
we were here?

04:26.717 --> 04:29.452
I paid some neighborhood kids
to call if anybody showed up.

04:29.520 --> 04:31.121
Little hoppers
deserve a bonus.

04:31.189 --> 04:32.923
Y'all didn't even
turn on the lights.

04:32.990 --> 04:33.957
Oh.

04:34.025 --> 04:36.860
I guess I can see why.

04:36.928 --> 04:40.096
We're not arsonists. It's, uh --
Not my business. Not why I'm here.

04:40.164 --> 04:41.665
Why <i>are</i> you here?
Well, you know,

04:41.732 --> 04:43.400
girlfriend here
helped spring me.

04:43.467 --> 04:46.303
But so far, being out
isn't much better than prison.

04:46.370 --> 04:49.372
I got a cop after me --
a dirty detective named Garza.

04:49.440 --> 04:51.274
Well,
that didn't take long.

04:51.342 --> 04:53.109
Hey. I've been keeping
my nose clean.

04:53.177 --> 04:54.344
This is old business.

04:54.412 --> 04:56.179
Garza's been haunting me
since I got home.

04:56.247 --> 04:58.014
Yesterday he caught up to me
on the street,

04:58.082 --> 04:59.182
told me point blank,

04:59.250 --> 05:00.684
"You're gonna wish
you stayed in."

05:00.751 --> 05:02.118
What do you think
he's gonna do?

05:02.186 --> 05:04.788
I don't know.
But I know I need help.

05:04.856 --> 05:06.523
It's just that right now's
not a good time.

05:07.959 --> 05:09.526
But we're gonna help you
anyway.

05:12.997 --> 05:14.164
Here's my number.

05:14.232 --> 05:15.265
[ Sighs ]

05:15.333 --> 05:18.034
Fi, can I talk to you
for a minute?

05:18.102 --> 05:19.703
Now is not a good time.

05:19.770 --> 05:21.204
You call me first thing.

05:21.272 --> 05:23.473
We'll go over the details,
and we'll get to work, okay?

05:23.541 --> 05:24.841
Thanks.

05:24.909 --> 05:27.444
I'll let you get back to...
whatever this is.

05:29.814 --> 05:31.181
[ Door closes ]

05:31.249 --> 05:32.549
What was that?

05:32.617 --> 05:34.184
We're supposed to be
playing dead.

05:34.252 --> 05:36.286
Well, I <i>would</i> have been dead
if it weren't for Ayn.

05:36.354 --> 05:37.654
She saved my life
in prison.

05:37.722 --> 05:39.155
I know the timing
isn't great,

05:39.223 --> 05:40.323
but her problem
isn't gonna wait

05:40.391 --> 05:41.691
till it's convenient for us.

05:41.759 --> 05:44.527
We can't go up against a cop
right now. We just can't.

05:44.595 --> 05:48.098
Fine.

05:48.165 --> 05:50.533
Well, if that's the way
you feel, I'll do it myself.

05:50.601 --> 05:53.203
What the hell
are <i>you</i> looking at?

05:53.271 --> 05:55.438
You're supposed to be
burning down my house.

06:05.393 --> 06:07.794
[ Cellphone rings ]

06:07.862 --> 06:09.496
[ Cellphone beeps ]

06:09.563 --> 06:10.630
Took you long enough,
bucko.

06:10.698 --> 06:11.898
It's not done yet.

06:11.966 --> 06:13.466
Then why are you interrupting
my "me" time?

06:13.534 --> 06:14.801
I found something.

06:14.869 --> 06:16.436
It looks like Westen
was putting something together.

06:16.504 --> 06:20.240
What? The --

06:20.307 --> 06:22.342
You know what? Never mind.
This isn't the time.

06:22.410 --> 06:23.610
You just go ahead

06:23.678 --> 06:25.412
and grab whatever's got
your panties in a bunch.

06:25.479 --> 06:26.413
Light a match.

06:26.480 --> 06:27.914
You can brief me tomorrow.

06:27.982 --> 06:29.149
[ Cellphone beeps ]

06:29.216 --> 06:30.917
Mission accomplished.
Card's spooked.

06:30.985 --> 06:32.952
Time to light this place up.

06:33.020 --> 06:34.220
[ Sighs ]

06:34.288 --> 06:36.556
We can take it from here.

06:36.624 --> 06:38.058
Why don't you
give us a minute?

06:47.568 --> 06:49.069
You okay? Are you okay?

06:54.508 --> 06:56.843
[ Sighs ]

06:56.911 --> 06:59.779
It's the only home
we've shared.

06:59.847 --> 07:00.780
It won't be the last.

07:05.553 --> 07:07.287
[ Breathes deeply ]

07:10.057 --> 07:11.391
[ Sighs ]

07:11.459 --> 07:13.660
[ Device beeps ]

08:03.978 --> 08:05.145
Thanks for waiting up.

08:05.212 --> 08:08.314
I'm sorry
we have to meet like this.

08:08.382 --> 08:10.083
This story
that we've all been killed --

08:10.151 --> 08:11.684
you won't have to pretend
much longer.

08:15.156 --> 08:16.856
You smell like a barbecue.

08:19.393 --> 08:21.561
Yeah, we had to...
burn the loft.

08:21.629 --> 08:25.331
"Had to."

08:25.399 --> 08:27.967
Just like you "had to" work with
the man who killed your brother?

08:29.136 --> 08:30.203
Did you think
I was stupid?

08:30.271 --> 08:32.806
You go to Panama
to catch Tyler Gray.

08:32.873 --> 08:34.607
It occurred to me
this morning...

08:34.674 --> 08:36.342
I haven't heard
his name since.

08:36.409 --> 08:37.910
I'm sorry.
I didn't want to --

08:37.977 --> 08:39.578
I know damn well why
you didn't want to tell me.

08:39.647 --> 08:41.748
Tom Card is the reason
Nate's dead.

08:41.816 --> 08:45.652
Tyler Gray is --
he's just a gun.

08:45.719 --> 08:48.521
Yeah, well,
I want to talk to the "gun."

08:48.589 --> 08:51.090
Mom, he won't be able to
give you the answers you need.

08:51.158 --> 08:52.625
Well, maybe not.

08:52.693 --> 08:56.596
But I lost my son,
and I get to ask the questions.

08:56.664 --> 08:58.097
Set it up.

09:00.734 --> 09:03.169
[ Indistinct conversations ]

09:03.237 --> 09:05.471
Well, your pal's got
a nice place here.

09:05.539 --> 09:08.374
I'm starting to think Mike had
the right idea opting out.

09:08.442 --> 09:09.475
[ Sighs ]

09:09.543 --> 09:11.244
He opted out
because he's being an ass.

09:11.312 --> 09:13.413
You know how many jobs
I've helped him with?

09:13.480 --> 09:15.348
Okay, but how many
of those jobs happened

09:15.416 --> 09:17.183
while you were
supposed to be playing dead?

09:17.251 --> 09:19.152
I mean, hell,
the only reason I'm here

09:19.220 --> 09:21.487
is to keep you from blowing up
a police station and blowing our cover.

09:21.555 --> 09:23.189
The point is, you're here.

09:23.257 --> 09:24.357
Yeah, well,
I wish I wasn't.

09:24.425 --> 09:25.825
I'm not too thrilled
about going to bat

09:25.893 --> 09:27.327
for somebody
who just got out of jail.

09:27.394 --> 09:30.697
Hi. Are you the people
who are supposed to help my mom?

09:30.764 --> 09:32.398
Yeah, we are.

09:32.466 --> 09:33.833
Right, Sam?

09:33.901 --> 09:35.468
[ Chuckles ]

09:35.536 --> 09:37.237
Hey.
[ Chuckles ]

09:41.909 --> 09:46.012
When I went in, Amari didn't
know how to ask for breakfast.

09:46.080 --> 09:48.715
Now he makes me eggs
every morning.

09:48.782 --> 09:51.618
I've already missed
too much of that boy's life.

09:51.685 --> 09:54.387
Tell us about this cop
that's coming after you.

09:54.455 --> 09:55.622
What's his problem?

09:55.689 --> 09:57.891
The man I went to prison
for killing.

09:57.958 --> 09:59.559
My brother-in-law, Marcus.

09:59.627 --> 10:01.694
He was
Detective Garza's C.I.

10:01.762 --> 10:03.796
And she's the good guy
in this scenario?

10:03.864 --> 10:06.099
Hey, I thought you said
this guy was cool.

10:06.166 --> 10:07.500
No, actually,
I'm <i>not</i> that cool --

10:07.568 --> 10:09.269
not when it comes
to killing police informants.

10:09.336 --> 10:10.570
How about wife-beaters?

10:10.638 --> 10:13.273
The son of a bitch
nearly killed my sister,

10:13.340 --> 10:15.008
and Garza let him do it.

10:15.075 --> 10:17.477
I guess you did
what you had to do.

10:17.544 --> 10:20.213
Why was Garza
protecting him?

10:20.281 --> 10:22.382
Marcus was feeding him dirt
on the Garden Terrace Mafia.

10:22.449 --> 10:24.050
Garza hates that crew.

10:24.118 --> 10:25.385
They killed his partner,

10:25.452 --> 10:27.587
and he's been out for revenge
ever since.

10:27.655 --> 10:28.955
Mom!
There's policemen outside!

10:34.895 --> 10:35.862
That's Garza.

10:38.365 --> 10:40.633
And he brought my P.O.
This is gonna be bad.

10:40.701 --> 10:42.268
He's gonna
violate my parole.

10:42.336 --> 10:44.604
Is there some other way
out of here, like a back window?

10:44.672 --> 10:46.272
They've all got bars
on them.

10:46.340 --> 10:47.707
Well, then, we're just
gonna have to bust out.

10:47.775 --> 10:49.242
Got a laundry room?
End of the hall.

10:49.310 --> 10:50.510
Okay.
We'll go out that way.

10:50.577 --> 10:52.679
I can't go with you.
Ayn --

10:52.746 --> 10:54.614
if I run from my P.O.,
I really <i>am</i> guilty.

10:54.682 --> 10:56.215
There'll be no way
to get me out.

10:56.283 --> 10:58.718
Amari will go
back into foster care.

10:58.786 --> 11:00.286
I can't watch that
happen again.

11:00.354 --> 11:02.355
Please, take him with you.

11:02.423 --> 11:04.590
Okay.

11:07.328 --> 11:11.497
We need to move it.
They're on their way up.

11:15.269 --> 11:17.070
Fi, give me a hand here.

11:19.873 --> 11:21.908
<i>Most</i>
<i>late-model washing machines</i>

11:21.976 --> 11:25.044
<i>spin at speeds</i>
<i>of over 1,200 rpms</i>

11:25.112 --> 11:27.380
<i>and create</i>
<i>more than 100 g's of force.</i>

11:27.448 --> 11:30.016
<i>That's more than enough</i>
<i>to rip off your finger...</i>

11:30.084 --> 11:32.986
<i>Or pull a curtain rod through</i>
<i>a couple layers of drywall.</i>

11:33.053 --> 11:35.421
[ Washing machine whirs ]

11:39.460 --> 11:41.894
[ Banging on door ]

11:41.962 --> 11:43.963
Hold on!
I'm getting dressed!

11:44.031 --> 11:48.001
Garza: Open up, Reeds! Come on!
I got your P.O. over here!

11:48.068 --> 11:49.535
Deny us entry,

11:49.603 --> 11:51.604
I'm gonna throw your sorry ass
back in jail. You hear me?

11:51.672 --> 11:52.739
[ Banging on door ]

11:52.806 --> 11:55.675
Jesus.
What are you, deaf, woman?

11:55.743 --> 11:58.044
Got a tip you were scoring drugs
down the block.

11:58.112 --> 11:59.312
Go on.
Search it.

11:59.380 --> 12:01.848
Is your boy here?

12:01.915 --> 12:03.349
Ayn: You leave my boy
out of this.

12:03.417 --> 12:04.717
I've never done drugs
in my life.

12:04.785 --> 12:06.052
You got no right
coming in here.

12:06.120 --> 12:07.086
[ Chuckles ]

12:07.154 --> 12:08.254
Back her up.
Back this girl up.

12:10.924 --> 12:13.459
Calm down, ma'am.
You need to calm down.

12:15.529 --> 12:16.796
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Look at this.

12:18.098 --> 12:20.133
Surprise, surprise.

12:20.200 --> 12:22.201
Looks like you'll be finishing
your sentence after all.

12:22.269 --> 12:23.636
That's not mine!

12:23.704 --> 12:25.071
Yes, it is.

12:25.139 --> 12:26.272
You kill a man, you do the time
and pay the price.

12:26.340 --> 12:28.307
He planted that!

12:28.375 --> 12:29.709
Shut your mouth.

12:29.777 --> 12:32.712
Okay, Amari. Here we go.
Just a little trip.

12:32.780 --> 12:34.981
Easy-peasy.

12:35.049 --> 12:36.516
[ Grunts ]

12:36.583 --> 12:38.117
Okay, yeah, yeah.
Don't -- don't get the neck.

12:38.185 --> 12:39.285
There we go.

12:39.353 --> 12:40.887
Garza: Now, go on.
Keep searching.

12:40.954 --> 12:42.822
The kid's got to be here
somewhere.

12:42.890 --> 12:45.258
Hang on, all right?
Here we go.

12:45.325 --> 12:47.760
[ Grunts ]

12:47.828 --> 12:49.595
Officer:
What the hell was that?

12:49.663 --> 12:51.898
Don't know.
Kid's not here.

12:51.965 --> 12:54.333
Let him be.
He's at his grandma's house.

12:54.401 --> 12:57.170
Don't tell me what to do,
killer. Now, let's go.

12:57.237 --> 12:58.604
I'm gonna take you
back where you belong.

13:10.875 --> 13:12.543
Sam:
There you go. Free candy.

13:12.611 --> 13:14.078
For real?
Yep.

13:14.145 --> 13:15.846
I'm friends with the lady
who owns this place,

13:15.914 --> 13:17.514
so you can have
whatever you want.

13:19.150 --> 13:22.019
Now, look, uh... I know you're
worried about your mom.

13:22.087 --> 13:24.455
But we're gonna get her out,
okay?

13:24.522 --> 13:25.456
I promise you.

13:31.796 --> 13:34.431
If you need this guy to cop to
planting drugs on your friend,

13:34.499 --> 13:36.100
blackmail
is the easiest way to go.

13:36.167 --> 13:37.735
You know
what I would like to do?

13:37.802 --> 13:39.770
I would like to march
into the nearest police station

13:39.838 --> 13:41.105
and tell them
that he's dirty.

13:41.172 --> 13:43.907
But I can't
because I am trapped

13:43.975 --> 13:46.110
in the world's nicest
safe house.

13:46.177 --> 13:48.445
Fi, what you need
is proof he's dirty.

13:48.513 --> 13:50.881
Garza's never been able
to find another C.I.

13:50.949 --> 13:53.384
to take down the crew
that killed his partner.

13:53.451 --> 13:54.618
Let's give him one.

13:54.686 --> 13:55.919
Well,
a new friend like that

13:55.987 --> 13:57.454
could talk him
into doing some dirt.

13:57.522 --> 13:59.390
Maybe steal some evidence
from police impound --

13:59.457 --> 14:00.691
that would be enough.

14:00.759 --> 14:03.794
But, of course,
the question is,

14:03.862 --> 14:08.399
who could pass
for a... gang member?

14:11.803 --> 14:12.570
What?

14:12.593 --> 14:13.410
Michael:
I hate to ask.

14:13.411 --> 14:14.345
Wow.

14:14.412 --> 14:15.746
Seriously? Guys?

14:15.814 --> 14:17.782
Now is good time
to go after a cop

14:17.849 --> 14:18.949
on behalf
of a convicted murderer?

14:19.017 --> 14:20.151
No, thank you.

14:20.218 --> 14:21.752
Garza doesn't deserve
to call himself a cop.

14:21.820 --> 14:24.021
And you're wrong about Ayn.

14:24.089 --> 14:26.290
She's a good person.

14:26.358 --> 14:27.591
She killed a guy, Fi.

14:27.659 --> 14:28.793
So, as a person,
I'd give her, like, a "C."

14:28.860 --> 14:29.794
C-plus tops.

14:29.861 --> 14:31.929
Jesse, if you don't help,

14:31.997 --> 14:34.832
that kid is gonna grow up
without a mother.

14:34.900 --> 14:36.100
[ Sighs ]

14:36.168 --> 14:37.868
You know something
about that.

14:37.936 --> 14:39.203
Just give me
the damn phone.

14:39.271 --> 14:41.205
Let me call this bastard
before I change my mind.

14:48.446 --> 14:50.347
<i>When posing</i>
<i>as a hard-core criminal,</i>

14:50.415 --> 14:52.183
<i>the key is to come on strong.</i>

14:52.250 --> 14:54.752
<i>You sit in the power position</i>
<i>in the room</i>

14:54.820 --> 14:56.987
<i>and take up as much space</i>
<i>as possible.</i>

14:57.055 --> 14:58.189
Detective. Yo.

14:58.256 --> 14:59.990
What's going on, baby?

15:00.058 --> 15:03.928
<i>And you never, ever show</i>
<i>any respect for the police.</i>

15:03.995 --> 15:05.429
I'm your date,
playboy.

15:05.497 --> 15:06.797
Lucky you, right?
Shh! Shh-shh-shh.

15:06.865 --> 15:08.232
You want to get down
on some food?

15:08.300 --> 15:09.900
Listen,
thanks for making the drive,

15:09.968 --> 15:11.502
but you got to keep your
goddamn voice down, all right?

15:11.570 --> 15:13.070
My bad.

15:13.138 --> 15:14.705
Waitress:
Here you go, Detective.

15:14.773 --> 15:15.973
How you doing?

15:16.041 --> 15:18.576
Jace Robinson's gonna solve
all my problems

15:18.643 --> 15:20.311
with the G.T. Mafia, huh?

15:20.378 --> 15:22.112
Don't be coming up in here
using my real name, man.

15:22.180 --> 15:23.981
I told you on the phone --
you call me J-Train.

15:24.049 --> 15:26.217
[ Laughs ]

15:26.284 --> 15:28.786
I think I would remember
an A.K.A. that stupid.

15:28.854 --> 15:30.621
We got no record of you.

15:30.689 --> 15:32.656
So,
who the hell are you?

15:32.724 --> 15:34.925
Look, I ain't gonna be
all up in your system, man.

15:34.993 --> 15:36.460
I'm new blood.
I'm from Queens.

15:36.528 --> 15:38.262
I wasn't getting my due
up in the Apple.

15:38.330 --> 15:39.597
I came down here last year.

15:39.664 --> 15:40.931
Ka-blooey.
I'm blowing up.

15:40.999 --> 15:42.733
You're "blowing up," huh?
That's right.

15:42.801 --> 15:44.201
And you thought
your next logical step

15:44.269 --> 15:45.436
is to become a snitch?

15:45.503 --> 15:47.471
Okay, "A,"
let's not use that word.

15:47.539 --> 15:48.806
That's an ugly word.

15:48.874 --> 15:51.475
"B,"
I want to be your C.I.

15:51.543 --> 15:53.544
Because the only thing
between me and the top

15:53.612 --> 15:54.845
is the boss.

15:54.913 --> 15:56.413
I can help you
take him out.

15:56.481 --> 15:58.849
You're gonna help me
take down Sherrod Washington,

15:58.917 --> 16:01.318
the man that killed
my partner?

16:01.386 --> 16:02.606
I think you're playing an angle,
and I don't like it.

16:02.607 --> 16:03.355
Of course
I'm playing an angle.

16:03.356 --> 16:04.789
What the hell
you think I'm doing?

16:04.856 --> 16:06.824
Look, Sherrod and his boys
go down,

16:06.892 --> 16:09.059
that's what you call
a regime change, son.

16:09.127 --> 16:10.694
Happens all the time.

16:10.762 --> 16:13.831
And guess who's got next.
Ooh. Ooh.

16:13.899 --> 16:17.301
You do this, Detective, you get
a nice, little, shiny medal,

16:17.369 --> 16:20.237
you get peace in the Terrace,
and you get a partner.

16:23.675 --> 16:24.808
How close to Sherrod
are you?

16:24.876 --> 16:26.243
What I say?
We tight, man.

16:26.311 --> 16:27.478
Okay.

16:27.545 --> 16:29.213
Let's go find out
how tight you are, huh?

16:29.281 --> 16:32.016
Yeah, let's do that.

16:39.157 --> 16:40.491
You want to work together,

16:40.558 --> 16:42.226
you're gonna have to
show me something, J-Train.

16:42.294 --> 16:44.828
Sherrod's bar
right behind me.

16:44.896 --> 16:47.197
You need to get inside
and go to his private office

16:47.265 --> 16:49.099
and take a picture of it
with your phone.

16:49.167 --> 16:50.467
Okay.

16:50.535 --> 16:52.403
Now.

16:52.470 --> 16:54.271
No problem, man.
I'll be back.

17:05.951 --> 17:07.284
Fi: Hey, Jesse.
How's it going?

17:07.352 --> 17:08.551
Uh, that depends.

17:08.619 --> 17:10.253
How fast can you get down
to Alize in Overtown?

17:10.321 --> 17:11.521
20 minutes.

17:11.589 --> 17:12.623
Better make it 10.

17:12.691 --> 17:14.058
Garza's got me
on a scavenger hunt.

17:14.125 --> 17:16.527
I got to get a picture of
the inside of Sherrod's office.

17:16.594 --> 17:19.630
It's guarded
by a gigantic human being.

17:19.698 --> 17:21.031
And judging by the looks
of this place,

17:21.098 --> 17:22.165
I'm betting it's locked.

17:22.233 --> 17:23.666
I'll be there.
Thank you.

17:30.875 --> 17:32.109
Here we go.

17:32.177 --> 17:35.612
Gray is headed over.

17:35.680 --> 17:37.715
<i>Hey.</i>
<i>Sorry I'm late.</i>

17:37.782 --> 17:38.983
<i>No worries.</i>

17:39.050 --> 17:41.919
<i>This is, uh...</i>

17:41.987 --> 17:44.054
<i>This is some heat we're having,</i>
<i>isn't it?</i>

17:44.122 --> 17:46.023
<i>It's fine with me.</i>
<i>I like sunny days.</i>

17:46.091 --> 17:47.958
What did he say?

17:48.026 --> 17:49.827
Something about sunny days.

17:49.894 --> 17:50.961
The weather.

17:51.029 --> 17:52.963
That's Card's
favorite recognition code.

17:53.031 --> 17:55.532
He had different signals
for all his field ops.

17:55.600 --> 17:57.001
What? Do you think we're blown?
I don't know.

17:57.068 --> 17:58.602
But he must be worried
someone's listening in.

17:58.670 --> 18:00.037
Wait, wait.
Mike, Mike, hang on. Hang on.

18:00.105 --> 18:02.606
I mean, maybe Gray's
just giving him the all-clear.

18:02.674 --> 18:05.075
Let's not jump ship
until we know where it's going.

18:06.945 --> 18:08.445
<i>See what I mean?</i>

18:08.513 --> 18:12.649
<i>Westen was looking for people</i>
<i>who wanted Anson dead.</i>

18:12.717 --> 18:13.817
<i>Long list.</i>

18:13.885 --> 18:15.052
I think he knew
you were on it.

18:17.422 --> 18:19.456
Why do you think
we closed the loop?

18:19.524 --> 18:22.192
It wasn't 'cause Michael
stopped sending me Christmas cards.

18:22.260 --> 18:24.895
I get it. But if he was onto you,
he might have told someone.

18:24.963 --> 18:27.331
It's under control.

18:27.399 --> 18:29.466
<i>Back off the caffeine,</i>
<i>champ.</i>

18:29.534 --> 18:32.302
Something is wrong, Sam.
He's soft-selling it.

18:32.370 --> 18:35.706
How about if we give the man
30 whole seconds to pitch this?

18:35.774 --> 18:37.107
If you're so confident,

18:37.175 --> 18:39.309
how come I'm pulling triggers
and burning lofts?

18:39.377 --> 18:40.844
That's a need-to-know,
Tyler.

18:40.912 --> 18:42.846
Well, whatever this is,
I'm a part of it now.

18:42.914 --> 18:45.049
There's blood on my hands.

18:45.116 --> 18:47.718
Read...me...in.

18:47.786 --> 18:50.254
Fine.

18:50.321 --> 18:51.455
But not here.

18:51.523 --> 18:52.890
<i>Friday.</i>

18:52.957 --> 18:54.591
<i>I'll show you the briefing</i>
<i>material, the whole lid.</i>

18:56.227 --> 18:58.629
We're done.
You'll hear from me.

18:58.696 --> 19:00.197
Okay. See?
He dialed it in.

19:00.265 --> 19:02.966
I think he just -- okay.
Damn it. Mike.

19:07.772 --> 19:10.074
What the hell was that?
What was what?

19:10.141 --> 19:11.775
We rehearsed this
five times.

19:11.843 --> 19:14.011
And in no version
was there a recognition code.

19:14.079 --> 19:14.945
I said no surprises!

19:15.013 --> 19:16.146
He asked about the heat.

19:16.214 --> 19:17.981
He wanted to know
if I'd been followed.

19:18.049 --> 19:19.683
I had to let him know
we were clear.

19:19.751 --> 19:21.819
You didn't push
for one hard piece of intel!

19:21.886 --> 19:23.554
If you're running
some double game --

19:23.621 --> 19:25.923
Back off!
I know what I'm doing!

19:25.990 --> 19:27.191
Card is spooked.

19:27.258 --> 19:29.560
If I had pushed too hard,
he would've shut down.

19:29.627 --> 19:30.861
Give me time.

19:30.929 --> 19:32.362
I'll reel him in.

19:32.430 --> 19:34.231
I will get what we need.

19:34.299 --> 19:35.632
You better.

19:47.545 --> 19:49.980
Oh, nice necklace.

19:50.048 --> 19:51.815
You know, I think I have
a matching bracelet

19:51.883 --> 19:53.317
if you'd like to borrow it
sometime.

19:53.384 --> 19:55.953
You got jokes.

19:56.020 --> 19:58.088
The office is back there.
The boss is over there.

19:58.156 --> 20:01.125
And beefy "T" has not moved
since I called you.

20:01.192 --> 20:03.794
[ Sighs ]

20:03.862 --> 20:05.095
Uh, champagne?

20:05.163 --> 20:07.331
The one on the top shelf.

20:07.398 --> 20:12.169
And can I keep
the cork and the cage?

20:12.237 --> 20:13.203
I'm a collector.

20:15.907 --> 20:17.274
Can we not celebrate
just yet?

20:17.342 --> 20:18.642
You still got to
pick your way in.

20:18.710 --> 20:20.377
Did you get some tools?

20:20.445 --> 20:21.912
What do you think
I'm collecting?

20:21.980 --> 20:24.281
Clever girl.

20:24.349 --> 20:26.717
So, how you gonna clear big boy
out of the way?

20:26.784 --> 20:29.286
I'll take care of it.
Wish me luck.

20:32.690 --> 20:34.291
Party people, what is up?

20:34.359 --> 20:36.093
[ Chuckles ]

20:36.161 --> 20:38.195
You.

20:38.263 --> 20:40.230
You.
You look like a player.

20:40.298 --> 20:41.632
Am I right, ladies?
Am I right?

20:41.699 --> 20:43.066
Is he a player?
Look at him.

20:43.134 --> 20:44.234
Why don't you
get up out of here, man?

20:44.302 --> 20:46.036
No, no. Shh. Listen.
Listen. Listen.

20:46.104 --> 20:47.304
Seriously.

20:47.372 --> 20:48.438
I'm down here from Jacksonville
on business,

20:48.506 --> 20:49.740
and I got a deal for you,
homey.

20:49.807 --> 20:52.075
My man said get out of here.
I need you to --

20:52.143 --> 20:53.744
Hey, Malik!

20:53.811 --> 20:55.379
No!
I didn't want to do that.

20:55.446 --> 20:56.180
Who's Malik?

20:56.247 --> 20:57.414
Hey, no, no.

20:57.482 --> 20:59.116
We don't need Malik
involved in this.

20:59.184 --> 21:00.517
No.
False alarm, Malik.

21:00.585 --> 21:02.152
We're good. We're good.
We're good. We're good.

21:02.220 --> 21:03.654
Back to your business.

21:03.721 --> 21:04.655
Bounce this fool.

21:06.424 --> 21:09.793
No, no bouncing. Look,
I just want to talk to you.

21:09.861 --> 21:11.695
[ Grunting ]

21:19.204 --> 21:22.039
When you in my club...

21:22.106 --> 21:23.040
You...

21:23.107 --> 21:24.508
Best...

21:24.576 --> 21:25.409
Listen!

21:30.748 --> 21:33.016
That was fun.
That was fun.

21:33.084 --> 21:34.785
We all learned some things.

21:34.852 --> 21:36.353
You guys don't like money.
I dig it.

21:36.421 --> 21:37.521
Don't let me see you again.

21:37.589 --> 21:38.855
That's some good advice.

21:40.225 --> 21:42.926
Here you go.

21:48.199 --> 21:51.034
Whoo.

21:51.102 --> 21:53.003
[ Chuckles ]
Hey, hey.

21:53.071 --> 21:54.037
So, what happened?

21:54.105 --> 21:55.472
What can I say, man?

21:55.540 --> 21:57.341
Sherrod loves his drink.
It's a party up in there.

21:57.408 --> 21:58.709
Right.
Did you get the shot or not?

21:58.776 --> 22:00.611
What?
The picture. Do you have it?

22:00.678 --> 22:03.780
Ah, yeah, yeah, yeah.
Yeah, man.

22:03.848 --> 22:05.382
Whoop. Boom.

22:05.450 --> 22:07.951
Just like you asked.

22:09.988 --> 22:11.021
All right, Mr. train.

22:11.089 --> 22:12.489
It looks like
you're for real.

22:12.557 --> 22:14.925
Why don't you
go take a nap somewhere?

22:14.993 --> 22:16.026
We'll be talking real soon.

22:16.094 --> 22:17.461
Can't wait.

22:22.400 --> 22:23.567
[ Groans ]

22:27.676 --> 22:30.010
I ju-- ow!
Ow! Ow!

22:30.078 --> 22:31.479
You should have
let me stop them.

22:31.546 --> 22:32.513
I could have stopped them.

22:32.581 --> 22:34.348
Yeah. That's debatable.

22:34.416 --> 22:37.151
That one dude was three bills,
easy.

22:37.219 --> 22:38.786
[ Groaning ] Ouch.

22:38.854 --> 22:40.521
I hate this job so much.

22:40.589 --> 22:42.490
Well, the hard part's over.
You're in.

22:42.557 --> 22:43.891
Now all you have to do

22:43.959 --> 22:46.193
is convince Garza to steal a gun
from police lockup,

22:46.261 --> 22:48.763
we'll get him on tape,
and Ayn gets her life back.

22:48.830 --> 22:50.030
Yeah, I get it.

22:50.098 --> 22:51.465
But if Garza catches me
wearing a wire,

22:51.533 --> 22:53.000
my kidneys are
gonna get another workout.

22:53.068 --> 22:54.535
You don't have to worry
about that.

22:54.603 --> 22:56.404
I have Sam
working on something.

22:56.471 --> 22:58.773
We're gonna catch the bastard
on tape from down the block.

23:04.446 --> 23:06.847
Hey, you want to help?

23:06.915 --> 23:07.948
Help do what?

23:08.016 --> 23:09.483
[ Laughs ] Smart man.

23:09.551 --> 23:10.718
Come over here.

23:10.786 --> 23:12.586
Always ask that question.

23:12.654 --> 23:14.755
I get myself
into so much trouble

23:14.823 --> 23:17.425
helping people with stuff
without asking what.

23:17.492 --> 23:19.560
Sit down.

23:19.628 --> 23:22.563
You want to help us take down
the guy that sent your mom to prison?

23:22.631 --> 23:24.598
Tell me what to do.

23:24.666 --> 23:28.235
Michael: <i>The two most challenging parts</i>
<i>of planting a listening device</i>

23:28.303 --> 23:30.938
<i>are quick concealment</i>
<i>and power.</i>

23:31.006 --> 23:33.574
<i>If your target</i>
<i>wears a radio for work,</i>

23:33.642 --> 23:35.242
<i>you can kill two birds</i>
<i>with one stone</i>

23:35.310 --> 23:38.813
<i>by bugging a duplicate power</i>
<i>pack and switching them out.</i>

23:38.880 --> 23:40.781
<i>Do it right,</i>
<i>and you get a bug</i>

23:40.849 --> 23:42.917
<i>that your target</i>
<i>carries everywhere he goes.</i>

23:42.984 --> 23:45.886
Okay.
Let's test it.

23:47.622 --> 23:48.823
Chicken butt.

23:48.890 --> 23:49.790
[ Laughs ]

23:49.858 --> 23:51.692
I read that, 10-by-10.

23:51.760 --> 23:52.827
You ready, Jesse?

23:52.894 --> 23:54.628
Yeah,
just give me the thing.

23:54.696 --> 23:57.965
Thanks --
for helping my mom.

24:00.469 --> 24:01.402
Sure thing, little man.

24:07.609 --> 24:10.010
[ Siren chirping ]

24:10.078 --> 24:13.113
[ Police radio chatter ]

24:13.181 --> 24:15.916
I asked you
to keep this on the low.

24:15.984 --> 24:17.418
You got me strolling
up to a police station?

24:17.486 --> 24:19.520
You lazy mother--
Don't you worry about it.

24:19.588 --> 24:22.456
No, no.
I'm worried about it.

24:22.524 --> 24:24.859
Matter of fact, give me
your phone and your radio.

24:24.926 --> 24:26.093
[ Laughs ]

24:26.161 --> 24:27.628
I'm serious.
Really?

24:27.696 --> 24:29.363
I'm turning
both them bitches off.

24:29.431 --> 24:30.831
I ain't getting bugged today.

24:30.899 --> 24:32.166
There.

24:38.139 --> 24:40.541
Wait. What?
You taking them apart?

24:40.609 --> 24:41.775
You're damn straight.

24:41.843 --> 24:44.111
My boy tiny's
doing 10 to 15

24:44.179 --> 24:46.313
because of some electronic
voodoo the Feds pulled.

24:46.381 --> 24:47.915
Just tell me
what we're putting on Sherrod

24:47.983 --> 24:49.283
so I can get the hell
out of here, man.

24:49.351 --> 24:50.022
Just a dime bag.

24:50.023 --> 24:51.878
I figure I can pull a street
rip later, and whatever I --

24:51.903 --> 24:53.287
A dime bag? Hell no.

24:53.288 --> 24:54.722
How am I
supposed to step up

24:54.789 --> 24:56.290
if Sherrod's gonna be
out on bail the next day, man?

24:56.358 --> 24:57.958
I could have framed him
for possession my damn self.

24:58.026 --> 25:00.127
I came to you to put him away
for good. Come on, now.

25:00.195 --> 25:02.596
What exactly
did you have in mind?

25:02.664 --> 25:04.331
You go get a gun
from an unsolved case.

25:04.399 --> 25:06.166
What? No.
I'm not doing that.

25:06.234 --> 25:07.635
You fire a few shots
into a phone book,

25:07.702 --> 25:09.069
I plant the shells
in Sherrod's desk.

25:09.137 --> 25:10.204
I said I'm not doing that.

25:10.272 --> 25:11.372
Planting a little weed
is one thing,

25:11.439 --> 25:12.673
but stealing evidence
from impound?

25:12.741 --> 25:13.440
That's too much.
Come on, man! Man!

25:13.508 --> 25:14.875
You got this rep

25:14.943 --> 25:16.710
like you this outlaw cop
who breaks all the rules.

25:16.778 --> 25:19.146
"Ooh, Garza, he's a bad man.
You better watch your ass."

25:19.214 --> 25:21.482
And now what? You scared?
I thought you did what it takes.

25:21.550 --> 25:23.717
I thought
you got things done.

25:23.785 --> 25:26.353
[ Sighs ]

25:26.421 --> 25:27.454
Fine.

25:27.522 --> 25:29.657
Yeah,
that's what I thought.

25:29.724 --> 25:31.425
Now, you meet me
at River Park -- 2:00.

25:31.493 --> 25:32.693
You bring the gun.

25:32.761 --> 25:34.261
We'll pop a couple off.
And we finish this.

25:47.676 --> 25:49.276
Well, where's Gray?

25:49.344 --> 25:51.378
He's down by the docks.

25:51.446 --> 25:53.047
Mom, are you sure
you want to do this?

25:53.114 --> 25:55.149
I <i>need</i> to do this.
I've seen this before.

25:55.216 --> 25:57.585
A victim wants to meet the
criminal, and it never helps.

25:57.652 --> 25:58.953
Michael, just stop.

25:59.020 --> 26:01.221
I just don't want you to put
yourself through something

26:01.289 --> 26:02.690
that's just
gonna make it worse.

26:02.757 --> 26:05.793
Trust me --
that's not possible.

26:08.663 --> 26:10.230
[ Sighs ]

26:18.506 --> 26:19.473
Gray: Ma'am.

26:19.541 --> 26:22.643
Madeline Westen.

26:22.711 --> 26:26.180
Thank you
for agreeing to meet.

26:26.247 --> 26:29.450
I want to start by saying
how sorry I am --

26:29.517 --> 26:30.718
I don't give a damn
about that.

26:30.785 --> 26:34.188
All I want from you
is honest answers.

26:34.255 --> 26:37.825
I want to know what goes on
in the mind of someone like you.

26:43.031 --> 26:44.732
What's your training?

26:44.799 --> 26:46.400
I was a sniper
in the Marines.

26:46.468 --> 26:48.168
Why'd you join the CIA?

26:48.236 --> 26:50.270
I wanted
to serve my country.

26:50.338 --> 26:52.673
That's all? Huh?

26:54.376 --> 26:58.312
Do you have a hard time
getting close to people?

26:58.380 --> 26:59.546
Bad childhood?

26:59.614 --> 27:01.649
Is that why
Card picked you?

27:01.716 --> 27:03.817
'Cause you like
hurting people?

27:03.885 --> 27:05.953
He picked me because I'm
very good at what I do.

27:06.021 --> 27:11.959
Then why did my son die...
If you're so good?

27:12.027 --> 27:15.596
I was worried
about the wind --

27:15.664 --> 27:18.232
speed,
trajectory, distance.

27:18.299 --> 27:21.368
And so I switched
to a higher-caliber gun.

27:21.436 --> 27:24.338
I knew it would go through.

27:24.406 --> 27:27.841
I took the shot anyway.

27:27.909 --> 27:28.909
It was my job.

27:28.977 --> 27:30.244
[ Sighs ]

27:30.311 --> 27:32.680
[ Voice breaking ]
Did you even know who he was?

27:32.747 --> 27:34.248
No.

27:34.315 --> 27:35.849
He was my baby boy.

27:35.917 --> 27:37.451
[ Sniffles ]

27:37.519 --> 27:41.055
He liked cars, action movies,
and graphic design.

27:41.122 --> 27:43.857
He loved his family.

27:43.925 --> 27:49.129
His name was
Nathaniel Elias Westen.

27:49.197 --> 27:53.500
The next time you fire a bullet
that could end someone's life,

27:53.568 --> 27:56.170
you know their name.

27:56.237 --> 27:58.038
Yes, ma'am.

27:58.106 --> 27:59.940
I'm sorry.

28:00.008 --> 28:00.841
[ Sighs ]

28:10.518 --> 28:11.719
Okay.

28:11.786 --> 28:13.053
It's been an hour.

28:13.121 --> 28:14.488
When are we pulling the plug
on "Candid Camera"?

28:14.556 --> 28:16.056
<i>As a spy,</i>

28:16.124 --> 28:18.759
<i>your job is often to get people</i>
<i>to break the rules.</i>

28:18.827 --> 28:21.662
Okay. That's him.
Here we go.

28:21.730 --> 28:23.964
<i>You use their greed,</i>
<i>their fear, or their rage</i>

28:24.032 --> 28:26.366
<i>to make them betray the things</i>
<i>they value most.</i>

28:26.434 --> 28:29.703
<i>With a professional spy</i>
<i>pushing them hard,</i>

28:29.771 --> 28:31.538
<i>most people</i>
<i>abandon their principles.</i>

28:31.606 --> 28:33.173
What the hell
is all this?

28:33.241 --> 28:35.809
<i>But sometimes,</i>
<i>very occasionally, they won't.</i>

28:35.877 --> 28:37.344
What's wrong with you?
You bring the gun or what?

28:37.412 --> 28:40.681
I thought about your plan.

28:40.749 --> 28:42.950
Sorry.
I'm not doing it.

28:43.017 --> 28:46.653
That's kind of the opposite
of what we wanted on tape.

28:46.721 --> 28:50.190
<i>And when a target decides</i>
<i>to stick to his principles,</i>

28:50.258 --> 28:53.227
<i>you can suddenly find a mission</i>
<i>going very, very badly.</i>

28:53.294 --> 28:54.695
What? Now all the sudden
you're Captain America?

28:54.763 --> 28:55.863
Please, I'm --
[ Grunts ]

28:55.930 --> 28:57.164
You don't think
I <i>can</i> be?

28:57.232 --> 28:58.532
Okay, what the hell?

28:58.600 --> 28:59.967
Hey, hey, Fi,
hang on. Hang on.

29:00.034 --> 29:01.101
Garza: <i>You think you know me?</i>
<i>You're wrong.</i>

29:01.169 --> 29:03.170
<i>Sherrod killed my partner.</i>

29:03.238 --> 29:04.738
He shot him down
in front of witnesses,

29:04.806 --> 29:05.939
<i>only no one came forward</i>
<i>to testify,</i>

29:06.007 --> 29:07.107
<i>so the case fell apart.</i>

29:07.175 --> 29:08.575
I had nothing to do with that,
man.

29:08.643 --> 29:09.977
You're all the same --
every C.I. I ever worked with.

29:10.044 --> 29:11.678
I'm not gonna make
this mistake again.

29:11.746 --> 29:13.364
Are you cracked?
I thought you wanted revenge.

29:13.389 --> 29:13.881
No.

29:13.882 --> 29:15.682
What I want is my partner --
you hear me?

29:15.750 --> 29:17.651
That's what I want.
I want my partner back.

29:17.719 --> 29:19.953
So, what? Now you folding up
shop? It's just a gun, man.

29:20.021 --> 29:23.157
I said I'm not stealing evidence
from any case to close mine.

29:23.224 --> 29:27.127
I'm not screwing cops.
I'm not screwing victims.

29:27.195 --> 29:28.362
That's not who I am.

29:28.429 --> 29:29.897
You want to run
the Garden Terrace,

29:29.964 --> 29:31.265
you might just
get your chance.

29:31.332 --> 29:32.900
But if I'm still alive
to see it,

29:32.967 --> 29:34.268
I'm gonna take you down,
Train.

29:34.335 --> 29:35.736
Okay, hold on.
We had a deal.

29:35.804 --> 29:37.838
<i>No.</i>
<i>Now we've got a new deal.</i>

29:37.906 --> 29:39.807
<i>You stay the hell away from</i>
<i>the Terrace this afternoon.</i>

29:39.874 --> 29:41.208
And keep your mouth shut.

29:41.276 --> 29:43.343
Oh, so, what? You gonna
take on Sherrod in his project.

29:43.411 --> 29:46.146
Well, his project
happens to be in my city.

29:50.418 --> 29:51.318
[ Engine turns over ]

29:51.386 --> 29:52.519
Hey, you go down there,

29:52.587 --> 29:53.821
you're gonna get thrown
off a roof, man.

29:53.888 --> 29:55.556
[ Tires screech ]
Yeah?

29:55.623 --> 29:57.891
Well, then maybe this time
he'll go down for killing a cop.

29:57.959 --> 30:00.160
[ Tires squeal ]

30:06.234 --> 30:07.734
Sam: Hey, man.

30:07.802 --> 30:09.736
My God.
That bastard's crazy.

30:09.804 --> 30:11.839
Yeah, well, he's not the bastard
we thought he was.

30:11.906 --> 30:14.441
He's gonna get himself killed
trying to bust Sherrod head-on.

30:14.509 --> 30:17.177
And if that happens,
Ayn rots in prison,

30:17.245 --> 30:18.612
Amari goes to foster care...

30:18.680 --> 30:20.781
And we got a cop killed.

30:26.238 --> 30:27.538
Michael:
Fi, what's wrong?

30:27.606 --> 30:31.242
Ayn's cop just chose
a very inconvenient time

30:31.310 --> 30:34.011
to decide to become
a better man.

30:34.079 --> 30:36.013
And that makes you upset?

30:36.081 --> 30:38.883
He's about to get himself killed
in Overtown.

30:38.951 --> 30:41.519
Sam and Jesse
are on their way,

30:41.587 --> 30:42.720
but I don't know
if they're gonna make it.

30:48.293 --> 30:50.795
[ Sighs ]
<i>Now</i> you're in?

30:50.863 --> 30:52.530
I should have been in
from the beginning.

30:58.170 --> 31:01.405
Jesse: Just make sure you approach
on Howard from the northeast.

31:01.473 --> 31:03.307
Yeah.

31:03.375 --> 31:04.642
Fi's on her way.

31:04.710 --> 31:06.210
She's bringing Mike
and a trunkload of weapons.

31:06.278 --> 31:07.545
[ Siren wailing ]

31:07.613 --> 31:08.846
Here comes Garza.

31:17.756 --> 31:21.125
Garza: <i>Our father which art in heaven,</i>
<i>hallowed be thy name.</i>

31:21.193 --> 31:22.426
<i>Thy kingdom me...</i>

31:22.494 --> 31:23.728
How close are Mike and Fi?
About five minutes.

31:23.795 --> 31:24.929
Okay.

31:24.997 --> 31:26.497
Well, I think
they're gonna be too late

31:26.565 --> 31:28.833
because Garza
is getting ready to die.

31:28.901 --> 31:33.304
...for they kingdom is the power
and glory forever and ever.

31:33.372 --> 31:34.372
Amen.

31:34.439 --> 31:37.408
Maybe he's...
just really religious.

31:40.479 --> 31:43.881
Sherrod, come out here and face
me like a man, you little bitch!

31:43.949 --> 31:45.716
Nope, you're right.
He's gonna die.

31:45.784 --> 31:47.818
Your time is up.

31:53.058 --> 31:54.392
Sherrod!

31:54.459 --> 31:55.993
<i>I know you're home!</i>

31:56.061 --> 31:57.862
Sam, we got to stop him.
With what? A butterfly net?

31:57.930 --> 31:59.864
Well, I'm not just gonna sit
here and watch a cop get killed.

31:59.932 --> 32:01.666
If he's not calling for backup,
I'll do it for him.

32:01.733 --> 32:02.934
[ Cellphone beeps ]

32:03.001 --> 32:03.968
<i>I'm taking you in!</i>

32:06.738 --> 32:08.673
There you are.

32:08.740 --> 32:10.841
Sherrod Washington,

32:10.909 --> 32:13.411
you're wanted for questioning
about your involvement

32:13.478 --> 32:15.479
in the sale and distribution
of cocaine.

32:15.547 --> 32:18.115
<i>You're wanted for questioning</i>
<i>about your involvement</i>

32:18.183 --> 32:19.984
<i>in the prostitution</i>
<i>of underage women.</i>

32:20.052 --> 32:22.286
And you're wanted
for questioning

32:22.354 --> 32:25.523
about your involvement
in the death of my partner,

32:25.590 --> 32:27.358
Officer Anton Sproles.

32:27.426 --> 32:28.592
I'm taking you in.

32:28.660 --> 32:30.394
Damn, Garza.

32:30.462 --> 32:34.198
You turned this place
into a ghost town.

32:34.266 --> 32:36.801
I guess we're just missing
a ghost, huh?

32:36.868 --> 32:38.436
You're just making things
easier on me, Sherrod.

32:42.674 --> 32:45.009
Good. Now I'm taking you in
for assaulting a police officer.

32:45.077 --> 32:45.810
[ Grunts ]

32:53.185 --> 32:54.618
[ Sighs ]
How's it going, boys?

32:54.686 --> 32:56.087
What?
Did you stop for coffee?

32:56.154 --> 32:57.888
Garza's over there
getting beaten to death.

32:57.956 --> 32:59.323
Jesse: Yeah, and they got no problem
doing it right out in the open.

32:59.391 --> 33:00.758
All right, then.

33:00.826 --> 33:02.326
Let's show them how
professionals send a message.

33:02.394 --> 33:04.195
Give me the radio.

33:04.262 --> 33:07.098
Fi -- that car.

33:07.165 --> 33:08.532
Jesse -- that car.

33:08.600 --> 33:09.400
Big?

33:09.468 --> 33:11.002
Bigger.

33:11.069 --> 33:12.703
Use the tracer rounds.

33:12.771 --> 33:15.006
When I open up, you join in.

33:15.073 --> 33:17.908
We'll make it look like hell
is raining down on their heads.

33:17.976 --> 33:19.310
[ Laughs ]

33:19.378 --> 33:21.112
Mike, I have so much more fun
when you're here.

33:28.987 --> 33:31.022
Hey.
Yo, hold up. Yo, hold up.

33:36.294 --> 33:37.261
[ Garza coughing ]

33:37.329 --> 33:38.529
Man,
you should have never

33:38.597 --> 33:39.930
stepped foot on the Terrace
by yourself.

33:39.998 --> 33:41.132
[ Gun cocks ]

33:41.199 --> 33:43.534
Attention,
Sherrod Washington.

33:43.602 --> 33:46.003
Step away
from the detective.

33:46.071 --> 33:47.571
Tell me you hear me,
Sherrod.

33:47.639 --> 33:49.206
We can hear every word
<i>you're</i> saying.

33:53.278 --> 33:54.245
Who is this?

33:54.312 --> 33:55.813
Well,
that's a good question.

33:55.881 --> 33:57.948
Allow me to introduce myself.
My name is...

34:00.986 --> 34:02.253
And I'm from
the Department of...

34:02.320 --> 34:03.287
[ Device beeps ]

34:05.657 --> 34:06.757
Whoa!
Whoa!

34:06.825 --> 34:08.426
You want to find out
where the next one is,

34:08.493 --> 34:09.793
or do you want to
back away?

34:09.860 --> 34:11.228
Y'all can have
this pig! We're out!

34:17.168 --> 34:19.370
No, I don't think so.
You're not going anywhere.

34:19.438 --> 34:21.472
What the hell
do y'all want?!

34:21.540 --> 34:23.974
I want you all to surrender
your weapons to Detective Garza.

34:24.042 --> 34:25.109
[ Sirens wailing ]

34:25.177 --> 34:26.811
After all,
he just arrested you.

34:29.514 --> 34:32.349
[ Tires screech ]

34:32.417 --> 34:33.918
You heard the man.
Drop your weapons.

34:33.985 --> 34:36.853
[ Gun clatters ]

34:36.922 --> 34:39.757
Thank you.
Thank you, whoever you are.

34:39.824 --> 34:40.925
Be good, Garza.

34:42.561 --> 34:43.627
[ Handcuffs clicking ]

34:59.511 --> 35:01.112
Oh, awesome!

35:01.179 --> 35:02.046
[ Chuckles ]

35:02.114 --> 35:03.280
Say, "thank you."

35:03.348 --> 35:05.015
Thank you.

35:05.083 --> 35:06.083
Sam: You're welcome.

35:06.151 --> 35:07.585
I don't know how you did it,
girl.

35:07.652 --> 35:09.587
When they pulled me
out of lockup this morning

35:09.654 --> 35:11.388
and said that I was free to go,
I thought,

35:11.456 --> 35:13.958
"that criminal
is stone-cold magic."

35:14.025 --> 35:15.226
Well,
I got a lot of help.

35:15.293 --> 35:16.861
I even got a little
from Garza himself,

35:16.928 --> 35:18.729
but you probably don't want
to hear about that.

35:18.797 --> 35:20.965
Oh, I think I do.

35:21.032 --> 35:24.768
Well, we tried entrapment,
and we were gonna blackmail him.

35:24.836 --> 35:26.203
That didn't happen.

35:26.271 --> 35:29.807
He just -- he just decided
to do this.

35:29.875 --> 35:31.675
Sometimes when you push people
past their limits,

35:31.743 --> 35:32.977
they realize
they have no business

35:33.044 --> 35:34.111
standing so close to the line.

35:34.179 --> 35:37.448
Well, good for him.

35:37.516 --> 35:40.017
Man learned something
took me six years to realize.

35:40.085 --> 35:43.287
Some choices we make...

35:43.355 --> 35:45.689
You want to take them back,
but you can't.

35:45.757 --> 35:48.659
I'm just glad
to have a second chance.

35:50.228 --> 35:51.228
Me too.

35:59.671 --> 36:01.138
[ Door opens ]

36:02.841 --> 36:04.408
Madeline: Michael.

36:04.476 --> 36:06.810
Michael: Hey, Mom.
Big day tomorrow.

36:06.878 --> 36:08.846
We start gathering evidence
against Card --

36:08.914 --> 36:11.115
the secrets he's keeping,
the reason Nate died.

36:11.183 --> 36:12.516
There's no reason
Nate died.

36:12.584 --> 36:14.084
I understand how you feel,
mom.

36:14.152 --> 36:16.253
I want you to know that
he's gonna pay for what he did.

36:16.321 --> 36:17.855
I promise you that.

36:17.923 --> 36:21.192
And all the things I've done,
they'll be worth it.

36:21.259 --> 36:24.094
Michael,
I'm leaving Miami.

36:27.465 --> 36:29.500
I guess that would be
a good idea.

36:29.568 --> 36:32.136
It will sell the story
that we really died in --

36:32.204 --> 36:35.172
No, it's no ruse.
It's permanent.

36:35.240 --> 36:37.041
Your Aunt Jill said
I could stay with her,

36:37.108 --> 36:38.776
and I've been missing her
for a long time.

36:38.843 --> 36:39.944
So, that'll work.

36:40.011 --> 36:41.312
Don't you think
it's a little drastic?

36:45.350 --> 36:48.352
I can't keep watching you
turn your soul inside out,

36:48.420 --> 36:50.788
working
with these monsters --

36:50.855 --> 36:53.657
Tyler Gray and Card
and whoever's next.

36:53.725 --> 36:55.359
It doesn't matter.

36:55.427 --> 36:58.495
There's no one next.
After this, no one.

36:58.563 --> 37:00.264
Right.

37:00.332 --> 37:02.333
I need you.

37:02.400 --> 37:04.068
I can't.

37:04.135 --> 37:06.270
I can't go on
living in a place

37:06.338 --> 37:09.440
where everything reminds me
of the sons I've lost.

37:09.507 --> 37:10.641
<i>I'm</i> still here.

37:12.277 --> 37:13.677
I don't know about that.

37:15.547 --> 37:18.482
I need a new beginning,
Michael.

37:18.550 --> 37:21.452
And I want you
to do me a favor.

37:21.519 --> 37:25.322
When this business with Card
is over...

37:25.390 --> 37:29.660
I want you to start over,
too.

37:36.351 --> 37:37.766
<i>When you're on a high stakes</i>

37:37.767 --> 37:39.735
<i>intelligence-gathering</i>
<i>operation,</i>

37:39.802 --> 37:41.103
<i>concentration is key.</i>

37:41.170 --> 37:43.438
<i>Whether you're in a car</i>
<i>or on the street</i>

37:43.506 --> 37:45.507
<i>or doing your surveillance</i>
<i>poolside,</i>

37:45.575 --> 37:47.442
<i>you have to stay focused</i>
<i>at all times.</i>

37:47.510 --> 37:50.212
Jesse: Look alive.
Gray's here for the meeting.

37:50.279 --> 37:52.881
All clear over here.
We'll stand by.

37:52.949 --> 37:54.850
<i>Because even</i>
<i>the slightest detail</i>

37:54.917 --> 37:56.385
<i>can mean the difference</i>

37:56.452 --> 37:58.754
<i>between a successful mission</i>
<i>and a complete disaster.</i>

38:02.058 --> 38:03.825
You're a little edgy there,
buddy.

38:04.081 --> 38:05.348
Don't.
We have a job to do.

38:06.531 --> 38:07.998
You're worried about your mom.
It's okay.

38:08.066 --> 38:08.999
It's perfectly normal.

38:09.067 --> 38:10.067
Quiet.

38:10.134 --> 38:11.468
[ <i>Knock on door, door opens</i> ]

38:11.536 --> 38:13.203
Card:
<i>Good to see you, Tyler.</i>

38:13.271 --> 38:14.338
<i>Another sunny day.</i>

38:14.405 --> 38:16.073
Gray:
<i>It's a scorcher.</i>

38:16.140 --> 38:17.708
<i>You gonna invite me in, or are</i>
<i>we gonna talk in the hallway.</i>

38:17.775 --> 38:18.875
[ Static crackles ]

38:18.943 --> 38:20.377
Okay. What the hell?
We just lost him.

38:20.445 --> 38:21.678
Wait. Is that?

38:21.746 --> 38:23.113
No signal.

38:23.181 --> 38:24.881
Frequency jammer.
That's not good.

38:27.819 --> 38:29.052
And that's not good,
either.

38:29.120 --> 38:30.787
Card brought a team.

38:30.855 --> 38:34.257
Wait.
Mike, hold on.

38:34.325 --> 38:35.559
Look, look,
if he wanted Gray dead,

38:35.626 --> 38:36.960
he wouldn't have brought
all these guys.

38:37.028 --> 38:38.061
He's not gonna kill him.

38:38.129 --> 38:39.329
He's gonna bring Gray in

38:39.397 --> 38:41.098
and hang everything
around his neck --

38:41.165 --> 38:43.133
Panama, Nate,
Anson, all of it.

38:43.201 --> 38:45.202
We got to haul Card
out in cuffs

38:45.269 --> 38:48.138
and take our chances now
before his team's in place.

38:52.276 --> 38:53.410
[ Elevator bell dings ]

38:58.316 --> 38:59.316
Keep an eye out.

38:59.384 --> 39:00.550
I should go in there
with you.

39:00.618 --> 39:02.486
If Card's people are coming,
I need a heads-up.

39:02.553 --> 39:04.488
Get down to the window
at the end of the hall

39:04.555 --> 39:05.622
and keep an eye out.

39:18.469 --> 39:19.436
Hello, there.

39:19.504 --> 39:20.504
Show me your hands, Tom.

39:22.106 --> 39:23.607
What are you doing?

39:23.674 --> 39:25.809
Gray, he has a weapon
trained on you.

39:29.180 --> 39:32.282
Michael Westen.

39:32.350 --> 39:33.383
Back from the dead.

39:33.451 --> 39:35.118
Not just me, Tom.

39:35.186 --> 39:36.787
The whole team.
It's over.

39:36.854 --> 39:38.221
The truth's coming out.

39:38.289 --> 39:39.489
Put the weapon down.

39:39.557 --> 39:40.357
Right.

39:40.425 --> 39:42.726
Right after you, killer.

39:42.794 --> 39:45.162
Tom, drop the weapon.

39:45.229 --> 39:48.532
This is between him and me,
sport.

39:48.599 --> 39:50.567
I should have known
something was going on.

39:50.635 --> 39:54.104
Especially with those
just-too-cute files

39:54.172 --> 39:55.138
that showed up
from your loft.

39:55.206 --> 39:56.406
Tom.

39:56.474 --> 39:57.974
Put the weapon down.

40:01.579 --> 40:02.512
Don't do --

40:02.580 --> 40:03.447
[ whistles ]

40:06.417 --> 40:08.919
What are you gonna do?
Shoot me?

40:08.986 --> 40:11.154
You're not the only guy in
the room who has a team outside.

40:11.222 --> 40:15.258
I told my people that I was
coming to see an unstable asset.

40:15.326 --> 40:16.893
God damn it!

40:16.961 --> 40:19.196
I don't want to do this.
I don't want to do this.

40:19.263 --> 40:20.363
I don't want to do this!

40:20.431 --> 40:21.531
Don't! Don't.

40:21.599 --> 40:24.367
I'm so sorry.

40:24.435 --> 40:26.236
He painted me into a corner

40:26.304 --> 40:28.205
the minute
he kicked down that door.

40:28.272 --> 40:29.639
No. No, Tom.

40:29.707 --> 40:31.241
He killed your brother!

40:34.679 --> 40:35.879
Hands on your head!

40:35.947 --> 40:37.881
Hands on your head!

40:39.150 --> 40:40.383
Listen to me, Michael.

40:40.451 --> 40:42.385
Gray killed Anson.
Gray shot your brother.

40:42.453 --> 40:44.688
He murdered Nate.
He did that.

40:44.755 --> 40:46.156
Right there.
He did that.

40:46.224 --> 40:48.625
You ordered him to.
You're responsible.

40:48.693 --> 40:50.560
I never wanted Nate dead.

40:50.628 --> 40:52.395
I would never
have taken that shot!

40:52.463 --> 40:53.663
You tried to have me killed.

40:53.731 --> 40:55.765
And that is
my own personal hell.

40:55.833 --> 40:57.901
It wasn't
supposed to go like that.

40:57.969 --> 40:59.002
You were like a son to me.

41:04.408 --> 41:07.043
[ Chuckling ] You are
out of your mind.

41:07.111 --> 41:11.314
We both know that it is a big,
bad world out there, Michael.

41:11.382 --> 41:14.317
And guys like you and me --
we make calls.

41:14.385 --> 41:15.485
We get up in the morning

41:15.553 --> 41:17.287
and we know the ends
justify the means.

41:17.355 --> 41:19.756
Why do you think Anson
had to go? I'll tell you why.

41:19.824 --> 41:22.259
Because he knew
what I had going on in Yemen,

41:22.326 --> 41:26.029
in China, in Pakistan.

41:26.097 --> 41:29.065
Someone has to carry the bag
on the front line.

41:29.133 --> 41:34.971
So...I pull the trigger on
a couple of really bad guys...

41:37.508 --> 41:39.242
...or we roll the dice

41:39.310 --> 41:41.645
on a couple
of really bad conflicts.

41:44.649 --> 41:46.216
You're talking about treason,
Tom.

41:46.284 --> 41:49.920
Michael, might be time for you
to grow up, my friend.

41:49.987 --> 41:51.288
You're not my friend.

41:51.355 --> 41:53.557
But I was.
And I damn sure can be again.

41:53.624 --> 41:55.926
We can do things, Michael --
great things.

41:55.993 --> 41:57.894
<i>Necessary</i> things.

41:57.962 --> 42:01.331
There's a long to-do list, and
there's nobody left to do them.

42:01.399 --> 42:03.133
You wiped out
the last batch.

42:03.201 --> 42:05.302
It's just you and me now.

42:07.471 --> 42:09.806
Clock's ticking.

42:09.874 --> 42:11.474
What do you think?

42:13.477 --> 42:17.047
Can we -- can we put
all this behind us?

42:17.114 --> 42:20.717
Huh?
Can we move into the future?

42:39.670 --> 42:40.670
I'm so proud of you, son.

42:42.440 --> 42:43.406
[ Gunshot ]

42:44.842 --> 42:45.875
[ Body thuds ]

